-- European Stocks Advance; Stoxx 600 Climbs 0.3 Percent
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2013-02-27T12:58:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-27/european-stocks-advance-stoxx-600-climbs-0-3-percent.html
European stocks rose, rebounding
from yesterday’s selloff, as companies from European Aeronautic,
Defence & Space Co. to Bouygues SA reported earnings that topped
analyst estimates.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index climbed 0.3 percent to
285.49 at 12:56 p.m. in  London , paring some of yesterday’s 1.3
percent decline. The gauge earlier today fell as much as 0.3
percent.  EADS advanced 7.6 percent to 37.50 euros while Bouygues
surged 11 percent to 21.45 euros.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  